 Pupils at Milton Junior School in Bulawayo on Thursday celebrated Africa Day by wearing African Attire. In The Picture Ms Molian Ngulube explains to ECD A pupils how traditional food is prepared. The school held a two hour show where pupils presented poems and about what Africa Day means to them. They also modelled in African Attire. The Event is meant to assist children to identify with their roots, grow up with pride and knowledge about being African.